    "Two years after they were recognized as refugees, the Refugee Protection Division (RPD) vacated their status.",
    "According to the RPD, Asha, and Alia were not Somalis but Kenyan citizens who entered Canada with a study permit using a different identity.",
    "In the view of the RPD, the fact that they lied about their country of origin was a crucial element affecting their credibility for fearing persecution.",
    "A photo comparison generated using facial recognition software was the primary evidence against them.",
    "122 In this example, the automated system did not make the final decision; it aided the RPD in their decision-making."
